'''
1. TWO POINTERS ----------

Two Pointers in real life:

Booking apps → matching seats / time slots efficientl
Banking systems → matching debit & credit transactions
Ride-sharing apps → matching drivers with riders by distance
Chat & cloud apps → syncing messages/files between two lists
Analytics systems → finding common users/items between datasets

Why used:

Avoids slow nested loops
Works fast on sorted data
Uses less memory
Scales to millions of records

One-line memory rule:

When you have sorted data and need pairs/ranges → use Two Pointers.

'''

# 1. Remove Duplicates from a Sorted Array

